review_blob: Not the beer for everyone, but one to be enjoyed by Barley Wine Ale enthusiasts. Color and aroma are excellent, with a pleasing finish. For the price, it beats out a lot off the more pricey high ABV barley wine ales.
Just had batch 11 from 2014. This is the way a high gravity stout should look and taste. Enjoyable from beginning to end. Drink this beer if you get the opportunity.
